EBOLA VIRUS: STABILITY (2)
==========================
See Also
Ebola virus: stability archive.950811
Source: Ethleen Lloyd, CDC Special Pathogens Unit, commenting at the
National Council for International Health, Alexandria, Virginia (USA) on 10
June 1996
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
---------
During the 1995 outbreak of Ebola virus in Zaire, discarded syringes
containing traces of blood were found on top of a cupboard in Kikwit
hospital, one month after they had been used. Ebola virus was isolated from
those syringes.
- Mod.JW
